        Quinocycle Sdn. Bhd. has been supporting Malaysian businesses with quality packaging solutions since 2010. From new corrugated boxes starting at RM 1.90 per unit to cost-effective used boxes from RM 0.90 per unit, we serve companies throughout Peninsular Malaysia—from Balakong and Kajang to Cheras and Seri Kembangan.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
        With a minimum order of just RM 1,000 and fast delivery times, we're your local partner for reliable packaging supplies.
      </p>
      <a href={WA_LINK} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary text-on-primary font-label font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors">
        Chat on WhatsApp
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">
      Frequently Asked Questions About Packaging in Malaysia
    </h2>

    <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
      What is the best packaging material for fragile items?
    </h3>
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      For fragile items, corrugated carton boxes combined with protective materials like bubble wrap or honeycomb panels provide excellent protection. Corrugated boxes offer structural integrity while bubble wrap cushions impacts. For electronics and ceramics, double-walled corrugated boxes (B-flute or C-flute) are ideal, often starting from RM 2.50-3.50 per unit.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
      How do I choose between new and used packaging boxes in Malaysia?
    </h3>
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Choose new boxes for retail, high-end products, and direct customer deliveries where presentation matters and affects purchasing decisions. Used boxes work well for internal logistics, warehousing, wholesale distribution, and B2B operations where aesthetics are less critical. New boxes in Malaysia start from RM 1.90 per unit, while quality used boxes are available from RM 0.90 per unit—an important consideration for cost-conscious businesses.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
      What is the minimum order quantity for carton boxes in Malaysia?
    </h3>
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Most wholesale suppliers in Malaysia, including Quinocycle, require a minimum order of RM 1,000. This typically translates to 500-1,000 boxes depending on box size and type. Smaller quantities may be available at higher per-unit costs, making bulk ordering essential for cost optimization.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
      Is packaging material recyclable in Malaysia?
    </h3>
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Yes, corrugated carton boxes are 100% recyclable and biodegradable. Malaysia has growing recycling programs, particularly in urban areas like Selangor, Klang Valley, and Balakong. Many businesses now use recycled content in their packaging to reduce environmental impact and appeal to eco-conscious consumers.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">
      How can I reduce packaging costs for my business?
    </h3>
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Reduce packaging costs by ordering in bulk for RM 1,000 minimum, using appropriately sized boxes to minimize wasted space, choosing used boxes for non-customer-facing applications, working with local Selangor-based suppliers to reduce delivery costs, and evaluating alternative materials. Honeycomb panels, for example, often cost less than bubble wrap while providing superior protection for certain applications.
    </p>
  </article>
